condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Agreements with Village Health Committees | Description :The Project Management Unit shall make a portion of theproceeds of the Financing available on a grant basis to each selected Village Health Committee by means of an Incentive Agreementexecuted between the Project Implementing Entity, through the Project Management Unit, and the selected Village Health Committee,all under terms and conditions set forth in the Project Operations Manual. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Use of Health and Nutrition Incentives | Description :Terms and conditions set forth in the Project OperationsManual shall include, inter alia, the Village Health Committee's obligations to: demonstrate on a quarterly basis, the achievementof the performance targets proposed in its respective Health and Nutrition Action Plans; to utilize the Health and NutritionIncentives in accordance with sound technical, financial, environmental and social standards and practices and with theAnti-Corruption Guidelines; to refrain from using the Health and Nutrition Incentives for the financing of any IneligibleExpenditure; to carry out all procurement related to activities to be financed by the Health and Nutrition Incentives inaccordance with the provisions set forth in the Project Operations Manual; and to maintain cashbooks and registers recordingfinancial transactions to demonstrate meeting the requirements of the Project Operations Manual, the resources, expendituresand full utilization of the Health and Nutrition Incentives by the Closing Date. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS
